    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Rinse your<strong> brown rice</strong>, add it to a pot with plenty of <strong>cold water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 20-25 min or until it's tender with a slight bite</p><p>Once cooked, drain, return it to the pot and keep covered until serving</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/korean-style-king-prawn-and-sweet-pea-pods-stir-fry-with-brown-rice/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil half a kettle</p><p>Top, tail, peel and chop your <strong>carrot[s] </strong>into thin batons</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/korean-style-king-prawn-and-sweet-pea-pods-stir-fry-with-brown-rice/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a high heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>carrot batons </strong>and cook for 4-5 min or until beginning to soften</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/korean-style-king-prawn-and-sweet-pea-pods-stir-fry-with-brown-rice/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Trim, then slice your <strong>spring onion[s]</strong> finely</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/korean-style-king-prawn-and-sweet-pea-pods-stir-fry-with-brown-rice/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Drain your <strong>king prawns</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/korean-style-king-prawn-and-sweet-pea-pods-stir-fry-with-brown-rice/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the carrot has slightly softened, reduce the heat to medium-high</p><p>Add your <strong>sweet pea pods </strong>to the pan with <strong>half </strong>the<strong> sliced spring onion </strong>(save the rest for garnish!)</p><p>Add your<strong> ginger & garlic paste</strong> and <strong>tomato paste </strong>with 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp</span>] <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>flour </strong>and cook for 30 secs or until fragrant</p><p>Tip: Be careful \u2013 the ginger and garlic will sizzle from the heat of the oil!</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/korean-style-king-prawn-and-sweet-pea-pods-stir-fry-with-brown-rice/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add your <strong>gochujang</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and your <strong>gluten free</strong> <strong>soy sauce</strong> with 150ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [200ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[250ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> and a pinch of <strong>sugar</strong> and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Add your<strong> king prawns</strong> to the pan and cook for 4-5 min or until the prawns are cooked through \u2013 this is your <strong>Korean-style</strong> <strong>king prawn & sweet pea pods stir-fry</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/korean-style-king-prawn-and-sweet-pea-pods-stir-fry-with-brown-rice/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>Korean-style</strong> <strong>king prawn & sweet pea pods stir-fry</strong> with the <strong>cooked rice </strong>to the side</p><p>Garnish with the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>sliced spring onion</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
